WILLIAM McCRAY v. STATE OF FLORIDA 26 So. (2nd) 507

January Term, 1946

May 24, 1946 Division A William McCrary, in proper person. J. Tom Watson, Attorney General, and Reeves Bowen, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. PER CURIAM:

Order denying writ of error coram nobis is affirmed because petition for the writ fails to allege facts which are sufficient to warrant the relief prayed.

So ordered.

CHAPMAN, C. J., TERRELL, BUFORD and ADAMS, JJ., concur.
